                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d630">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6359 Wolfram Ore/58: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peck</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-25T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 25, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>78. Your 253, April 11, 3 p.m., in regard to tungsten ore. Although we appreciate
                    the force of your suggestions with regard to the manner of handling this matter,
                    it is our opinion that an approach along the lines set forth in the Department’s
                    65, April 8, 3 p.m., should be made. Such an approach would serve the purpose of
                    placing on record with the Chinese Government our position with regard to this
                    matter and of emphasizing our interest, which is especially important, <pb
                        facs="0671" n="667" xml:id="pg_667"/> in the commodity under reference and
                    our solicitude that American companies might as a result of action by the
                    Chinese Government experience difficulty in obtaining supplies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
